properties.headline: Special Weather Statement issued January 8 at 10:11AM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
This is a special weather statement from the National Weather
Service Office in Riverton.

* WHAT...Southwest winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts to 50 to 55 mph.
Occasional gusts of 55 to 60 mph are possible in favored areas
like Wyoming Boulevard south of Casper.

* WHERE...Along the Highway 287 corridor from Beaver Rim to
Jeffrey City and along the Highway 220 corridor, from Alcova to
Casper and Wyoming Boulevard south of Casper.

* WHEN...Through 6 pm today.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Anyone traveling along Highway 20/26, 220,
287 and Interstate 25 on Tuesday should anticipate sudden
strong cross winds.
